</li><br /><br />
<b>Observation #2 Adjective Agreement</b><br />
<b>English</b><br /> 

   The adjective does not change when the noun changes.<br />
 Adjectives do not become plural or change gender. 
<br /><br />
<b>Other languages</b><br /> 
The adjective changes if the noun changes.  <br />Adjectives agree with nouns in 
    gender (masculine, feminine) and<br />
    number (singular, plural)<br /><br />

<li>So they must know four forms for every adjective that they know in Latin:</li><br />
         masc. sg.(bonus) masc. pl.(boni)<br />
 fem. sg.(bona) fem. pl.(bonae)



</ul>


