Look at the chart of articles on p. 46<br /><br /></li>
<li>Articles: definite (the) and indefinite (a, an) do not exist in Latin. We have to supply them when we translate into English.
</li>
<li>The definite articles in the Romance languages, however, come from the Latin word for that, ille / illa and the indefinite come from the number one.
o Note that the articles in these languages change gender and number, as do their adjectives.
</li>
<li>English articles do not change gender and number.</li>
